                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>HEZEKIAH SHEPHERD. I am an <rs id="t18200918-238-viclabel1374" type="occupation">assistant at a school</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-238-victim2264 t18200918-238-viclabel1374"></join>. On the 13th of September, about ten o'clock in the morning, I was in the <placeName id="t18200918-238-crimeloc1375">Commercial-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-238-crimeloc1375" type="placeName" value="Commercial-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-238-crimeloc1375" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-238-off1372 t18200918-238-crimeloc1375"></join>. A procession was going to her Majesty. I felt my watch drawn from my pocket, and saw the prisoner running two or three yards from me. I followed, called Stop thief! he ran about twenty yards off, without my losing sight of him, - he struggled to get away. The watch was dropped close by where I stopped him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-238-person2265">
                  HENRY 
                  WHITE
               <interp inst="t18200918-238-person2265" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-238-person2265" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-238-person2265" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a ribbon-weaver, and live in Quaker-street. I was in the Commercial-road, and picked the watch up in the kennel, just by the prisoner, and delivered it to the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-238-person2266">
                  JOHN 
                  STARKEY
               <interp inst="t18200918-238-person2266" type="surname" value="STARKEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-238-person2266" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-238-person2266" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. The prosecutor gave the prisoner in charge for stealing his watch, he begged his pardon, and said,</p>
               <p>"You have got your watch, let me go."</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182009180093"></xptr>Prisoner's Defence. I did not take it, others were running as well as me.</p>
